# 📄 PPT to PDF Converter – Python + comtypes (Windows Only)

A lightweight and reliable tool to convert `.pptx` files to `.pdf` using Python.  
No content corruption. No external tools. Just pure Python and `pip` installable libraries.

---

## ✅ Features

- 🔁 Convert PowerPoint `.pptx` files to PDF formats
- 🔒 Ensures the output PDF is not corrupted
- 📦 Uses only `pip` installable libraries (no third-party software)
- 📄 Clean and simple script
- 🪟 **Works only on Windows** (requires Microsoft PowerPoint)

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Tool                 | Description                                  |
|----------------------|----------------------------------------------|
| Python 3.x           | Programming language                         |
| `comtypes` (via pip) | Windows COM interface to automate PowerPoint |
| Microsoft PowerPoint | Required backend engine                      |

---

## 📥 Installation

```bash
# Step 1: Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/ppt-to-pdf-converter.git
cd ppt-to-pdf-converter

# Step 2: Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

#project Structure

ppt-to-pdf-converter/
│
├── convert.py           # Main Python script
├── requirements.txt     # All pip dependencies
├── sample.pptx          # Example PowerPoint file
└── README.md            # Project documentation

Notes:

This script works only on Windows, as it uses Windows COM automation via PowerPoint.
Does not work on macOS or Linux, even with comtypes.
